text: The 1999 Hart Council election took place on 6 May 1999 to elect members of Hart District Council in Hampshire, England. One third of the council was up for election and the council stayed under no overall control. After the election, the composition of the council was *Conservative 16 *Liberal Democrat 14 *Independent 5 ==Election result== ==Ward results== ==References== 1999 Category:1999 English local elections Category:1990s in Hampshire
